    Substitute memset/memcpy calls with faster alternatives (#196)
    
    This patch adjustments the function call detection procedure due to
    the use of the jal instruction for function calls in RISC-V. The
    identification of mem{set,cpy} has been enhanced by analyzing the
    pattern of the initial basic block of mem{set,cpy} for comparison.
    When the pattern matches, the instruction sequence starting from the
    initial PC of the basic block is extracted and compared with the
    pre-recorded mem{set,cpy} instruction sequence. If a mem{set,cpy} is
    detected, the basic block is substituted with the standard library function
    mem{set,cpy}.
    
    This modification has led to a 2% performance improvement in CoreMark
    and Dhrysone benchmarks. The change in performance is attributed to
    the reduction in the number of memset/memcpy invocations.
    
    |   Metric   | origin  | proposed |Speedup|
    |------------| ---------| ---------| -------|
    | Dhrystone  | 1413.11 | 1447.11  |  +2%  |
    | CoreMark   | 1497.35 | 1525.31  |  +2%  |
    
